The global aluminum food cans market is segmented by type into two-piece cans and three-piece cans. Two-piece cans are usually made from aluminum and are advantageous in terms of cost and being lightweight. Three-piece cans are typically made from steel and are known for their superior strength. Based on capacity, the market is segmented into cans with a capacity of less than 100 ml, 100 ml to 300 ml, 300 ml to 500 ml, and more than 500 ml. When looking at end-use, aluminum food cans are used extensively in the food industry to store items such as fruits, vegetables, and pet food. They are also commonly employed in the beverage sector for packaging items like energy drinks and carbonated beverages. Additionally, aluminum food cans have found applications in the pharmaceutical industry for storing medicines.

